headline: W. R. Berkley (NYSE:WRB) Surprises With Q3 Sales
summary: Property casualty insurer W. R. Berkley (NYSE:WRB) reported Q3 CY2025 results exceeding the market’s revenue expectations, with sales up 10.8% year on year to $3.77 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $1.10 per share was in line with analysts’ consensus estimates.

Berkley announced its third-quarter earnings on Monday, with analysts expecting revenue to grow by 9% year over year to US$3.71 billion, although this represents a slowdown from the prior year’s pace.
